The paper deals with efficient generation of random walks in big graph models, which is a problem in distributed computing and graph algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the PageRank algorithm, which is a popular topic in information retrieval and web search, falling under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses property testing algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
